OK, the TF port on Windows is actually running in a psuedo UNIX 
environment.  That said, yes it's possible, but I wouldn't recommend this to
Ken.  Ken has said he is considering a different I/O layer for 5.0 anyways, 
so your request may be rendered irrelevant.  Anyways, if you REALLY want a
real scrollback function in NT/9X, the solution is very easy.  

run in /visual off,  prior to opening your TF app, type mode con: lines=100
resize the window border to whatever you wish, and poof, you have a 
scrollback.  Windows 9X limits this because it's Console is garbage, but NT 
can have very large scroll's and buffers. 

I happen to hope that TF 5 breaks from the BSD tradition of Sockets as File
Descriptors and adapts to using recv/send for socket I/O so that we can do 
away with the Cygnus workarounds and pick up a couple of additional platforms
as well.  But that is Ken's decision, and I doubt 5 will see the light for a 
few months still, while 4.0 is approaching 'Gold' status.

