> what about the prompt under my visual line AND the kicking off of the
> buffer from the second character so I don't get that backlog of scroll
> that comes on when I switch 

/fg -q dumps all buffered output when you switch worlds.
You can also use esc-j (or esc-J - see /help flush and /help selflush)
to dump everything behind the More prompt after you switch, assuming
you have /more on.

As for the prompt that shouldn't be there, recent versions of TF now
more intelligently attempts to determine the type of world you are on,
and whether it should have an lp-style prompt.  You can prevent much of
this from happening by using a -T flag for all your /addworld lines
(see /help addworld).


