TF supports TELNET_GA [telnet go-ahead] feature, farest i know, all ROM 2.4
muds have it implemented as a flag but there is no command to toggle it for
player, i added it to our mud, but it isn't default feature on ROM, i figured
way around it, from telnet.h you can get this 2 lines:

#define IAC     255             /* interpret as command: */
#define GA      249             /* you may reverse the line */

this is from kens tf help file:

  GOAHEAD: Send IAC GA (\377 \371) after each prompt.  This is the easier of
  the two options.  In many servers, this can be done at the beginning of the
  routine that reads user input.  Disadvantage: could possibly cause problems
  in clients that don't understand TELNET protocol (but usually, they will
  just pass it through to the terminal, which will usually ignore it).

so what you need to do is set your prompt on the mud where you playing and add
3 characters on the end of the prompt:

IAC GA which is 255 249 in ASCII scan codes

i use linux telnet client to do that, but i'm sure that there is a way to do
that in TF too somehow ;)

okay, by now you probably thinking 'what the hell he is talking about' :)
here is how it works: after you add the 2 chars on the end of the prompt TF
will recognize them and filter all prompts from output part of the screen, 
you will still be able to see the prompts in your input lines, like it should
be from beginning. 99% of the muds doesn't filter high ascii chars from player
files, and all pfiles are saved in text format, strings in pfiles are usually
terminated with ~ [tilde], so high ASCII chars aren't filtered or altered any
way. Or instead sneaking it in the prompt, you could ask imms on your mud to
add it to the code, it takes just about 5 mins to do it ;)

i use this on every mud where i can sneak it in the prompt or set it in my
player settings.

