Put this script somewhere in your path, call it tfrepeat and make
sure it's chmod +x and the path to perl version 5.x is correct:

-- cut here --
#!/usr/local/bin/perl -w

use strict;

unless (defined $ARGV[2]) {
  print STDERR "Incorrect number of parameters.\n",
               "syntax: tfrepeat ppid delay iterations\n";
}

my ($tf_pid, $delay, $iterations) =3D @ARGV;

if(!fork) {
  while ($iterations--) {
    kill 'USR1', $tf_pid;
    select(undef, undef, undef, $delay);
  }
}

exit 0;
-- cut here --

Now, use this macro:

/def -i mrepeat =3D \
  /if (!{2}) \
    /echo -e mrepeat: syntax, /%0 time count command%;\
  /endif%;\
  /let _time=3D%1%;\
  /let _count=3D%2%;\
  /if /ismacro -msimple -h'SIGUSR1'%;/then \
    /echo -e SIGUSR1 already taken or another %0 is running.%;\
    /break%;\
  /endif%;\
  /def -n%_count -h'SIGUSR1' mrepeat_body =3D %{-2}%;\
  /sys tfrepeat \$PPID %_time %_count

