With these known problems with snooping in several MUDs, I'm suggesting
two new functions,

 encrypt(s, t)
	(str) Returns the string <s> encrypted by the key <t> ("garbage")
 decrypt(s, t)
	(str) Returns the string <s> decrypted by the key <t> ("plain text")

I'm no expert on crypting so I can't suggest any algorithms, but there should
be some decent ones without export- or other restrictions. Security isn't
that huge issue here anyway.


I was thinking of construction like this:

/def ctell = tell player crypt: $[encrypt({-1},"fU6a|g")]
/def -ag -mregexp -t'^You tell Player \'crypt: (.*)\'' showowntell = /let msg=You tell Player '$[decrypt({P1},"fU6a|g")]'%;/echo %msg%;/test fwrite("tells", msg)
/def -ag -mregexp -t'^Player tells you \'crypt: (.*)\'' showtellfromplayer = /let msg=Player tells you '$[decrypt({P1},"playerkey")]'%;/echo -aB %msg%;/test fwrite("tells", msg)

So for ex. a:

Player tells you 'crypt: &1fAS&/5|¤'

is successfully echoed and logged

